com.threecubed.auber.pathfinding

Class NavigationMesh

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.threecubed.auber.pathfinding.NavigationMesh

  • public class NavigationMesh
extends java.lang.Object
    The NavigationMesh class is a wrapper around a 2d array of Booleans representing which tiles within the game world are accessible. It reads in a TiledMapTileLayer in order to produce this array of booleans. If a given set of coordinates do not have a tile, it is considered inaccessible. For this reason, the background layer of the map is used as the input for the navigation mesh. The class also contains functions required to facilitate A* pathfinding which entities that inherit from Npc make use of.
    Since:
    1.0

      • NavigationMesh

        public NavigationMesh(com.badlogic.gdx.maps.tiled.TiledMapTileLayer navigationLayer)
        Produce a navigation mesh from a given TiledMapTileLayer. This works by iterating over the given layer and appending either true or false to the mesh based upon whether a tile is present at the current coordinates
        Parameters:
        navigationLayer - The layer to produce a navigation mesh from
